# Regression: the contextual-noun soft keywords `default`, `end`, `query` and
# `view` must parse as plain identifiers in every identifier position — as
# struct field names in a `type` declaration, as field names in a field-init
# construction (`Cfg(query is 3, view is 4)`), as field access after `.`, as
# parameter names, and as bare variables in expression-atom position
# (`end - default`). They lex as keywords for their statement/clause roles
# (`query ... view ...`, `do ... end`, default-clause) but must never shadow an
# identifier where one is expected.

type Cfg
    query as i64
    view as i64

*span(default as i64, end as i64) returns i64
    end - default

*main
    c is Cfg(query is 3, view is 4)
    log(c.query + c.view)
    log(span(2, 10))
